'''Bilal El Khannouss''' ({{langx|ar|بلال الخنوس}}; born 10 May 2004) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[VfB Stuttgart]] and the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].

==Club career==
===Genk===
El Khannouss joined [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] in 2009, but moved to [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]] in 2019 due to a lack of playing opportunities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.anderlecht-online.be/nl/article/182752|title=El Khannous verlaat Anderlecht|website=anderlecht-online.be}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://sporza.be/nl/2024/04/30/el-khannouss-toverde-als-piepjong-rsca-talent-met-lavia-en-sadiki-ik-herinner-me-die-actie-nog~1714462669236/ |title=El Khannouss toverde als piepjong RSCA-talent met Lavia en Sadiki: "Ik herinner me die actie nog" |website=[[Sporza]] |language=nl |date=30 April 2024 |accessdate=26 September 2025 }}</ref> On 24 July 2020, he signed his first professional contract.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.krcgenk.be/nl/nieuws/3953/jeugdinternational-bilal-el-khannouss-16-tekent-eerste-contract|title=Jeugdinternational Bilal El Khannouss (16) tekent eerste contract &#124; KRC Genk|first=Sanmax|last=Projects|website=krcgenk.be}}</ref> He made his league debut on 21 May 2022 in a 0–0 draw against [[K.V. Mechelen|Mechelen]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hbvl.be/cnt/dmf20220521_97527614 |title=ONZE PUNTEN. Niet de avond van Paul Onuachu, knap debuut van Bilal El Khannous|website=hbvl.be|date=21 May 2022 }}</ref>

On 1 November 2023, El Khannouss was nominated for the 2023 African Young Player of the Year by [[Confederation of African Football|CAF]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=11 January 2023 |title=CAF announces CAF Awards 2023 Nominees for Men's Categories |url=https://www.cafonline.com/news/caf-announces-caf-awards-2023-nominees-for-men-s-categories/ |access-date=2023-11-01 |website=CAF |language=en-GB}}</ref>

===Leicester City===
El Khannouss signed for [[Premier League]] club [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] on 29 August 2024 on a four-year deal for a reported £21m fee.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=29 August 2024 |title=Bilal El Khannouss Signs Four-Year Deal |url=https://www.lcfc.com/pages/en/media-article/bilal-el-khannouss-signs-four-year-deal-with-leicester-city |access-date=2025-01-13 |website=lcfc.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=29 August 2024 |title=Bilal El Khannouss: Leicester sign Morocco midfielder from Genk for £21m |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cn87z47qj20o |access-date=2025-01-13 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He was assigned the number 11 shirt.<ref name=":0" /> El Khannouss made his Leicester debut on 31 August 2024 in a 2–1 loss against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=31 August 2024 |title=Cooper Disappointed With Villa Outcome |url=https://www.lcfc.com/pages/en/media-article/cooper-disappointed-with-villa-outcome |access-date=2025-01-13 |website=lcfc.com |language=en}}</ref> His first start came in a 1–1 draw against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] on 21 September 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/first-bilal-el-khannouss-start-9572552 |title=First Bilal El Khannouss start didn't go as Steve Cooper planned – but it wasn't his fault |author=Jordan Blackwell |website=Leicester Mercury |date=22 September 2024 |access-date=4 December 2024 }}</ref> He scored his first goal for the Foxes on 3 December 2024 in a 3–1 home league victory against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/dec/03/leicester-west-ham-premier-league-match-report|title= Vardy starts Van Nistelrooy welcoming party as Leicester add to West Ham woe|last=Lansley|first=Peter|website=The Guardian|date=3 December 2024|access-date=4 December 2024}}</ref>

===VfB Stuttgart===
On 1 September 2025, El Khannouss joined [[VfB Stuttgart]] on loan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2526/bilal-el-khannouss-traegt-ab-sofort-weiss-und-rot-/|title=VfB sign Bilal El Khannouss on loan|website=VfB Stuttgart|date=1 September 2025|access-date=1 September 2025}}</ref> Later that month, on 19 September, he scored his first goal in a 2–0 victory over [[FC St. Pauli|St. Pauli]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/746753/st-pauli-vfb-stuttgart |title=VfB Stuttgart 2–0 St. Pauli |publisher=ESPN |date=19 September 2025 }}</ref> On 25 May 2026, his loan spell was made permanent as he signed a long-term contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/neues/profis/2526/feste-verpflichtung-von-bilal-el-khannouss/ |title=Feste Verpflichtung von Bilal El Khannouss |publisher=VfB Stuttgart |language=de |date=25 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Belgium, El Khannouss is of Moroccan descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.footnews.be/news/248741/un-joueur-de-genk-prefere-le-maroc-a-la-belgique|title=Un joueur de Genk préfère le Maroc à la Belgique|website=footnews.be}}</ref> A former youth international for Belgium, El Khannous switched to represent the [[Morocco national under-20 football team|Morocco U20]]s.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lionsdelatlas.ma/coupe-arabe-u20-les-lionceaux-se-preparent-au-festin-face-aux-requins-du-djibouti/|title=Coupe arabe U20 : Les Lionceaux se préparent au festin face aux Requins du Djibouti|first=Lions De|last=l'Atlas|date=22 June 2021}}</ref>

On 10 November 2022, he was named in Morocco's 26-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Morocco World Cup 2022 squad: Who's in and who's out? {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en-bh/lists/morocco-2022-world-cup-squad-hakimi-ziyech-mazraoui-qatar/blta36257fc4feeb66a |access-date=10 November 2022 |website=Goal (website)}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=10 November 2022 |title=Moroccan coach unveils list of 26 Atlas Lions in 2022 World Cup |url=https://en.hespress.com/52697-moroccan-coach-unveils-list-of-26-atlas-lions-in-2022-world-cup.html |access-date=10 November 2022 |website=HESPRESS English – Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref> On 17 December, he made his international debut in the World Cup third-place playoff against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], which ended in a 2–1 defeat.<ref>{{cite web |author=Bart De Vré |url=https://www.voetbalkrant.com/nieuws/2022-12-17/bilal-el-khannouss-racing-genk-maakte-een-prima-debuut-voor-marokko-zeker-geslaagd |title=Bilal El Khannouss, Racing Genk, maakte een prima debuut voor Marokko: "Zeker geslaagd" |website=voetbalkrant.com |language=nl |date=17 December 2022 }}</ref>

In June 2023, he was included in the final squad of the [[Morocco national under-23 football team|under-23 national team]] for the [[2023 U-23 Africa Cup of Nations]], hosted by Morocco itself,<ref>{{Cite web |date=9 June 2023 |title=Sei bianconeri con le nazionali |url=https://www.fclugano.com/sei-bianconeri-con-le-nazionali-2/ |access-date=27 June 2023 |website=[[FC Lugano]] |language=it-CH |archive-date=27 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240527002315/https://www.fclugano.com/sei-bianconeri-con-le-nazionali-2/ |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=24 June 2023 |title=تشكيلة المنتخب الوطني لاقل من 23 سنة امام غينيا |url=https://site.frmf.ma/%d8%aa%d8%b4%d9%83%d9%8a%d9%84%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d9%86%d8%aa%d8%ae%d8%a8-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%88%d8%b7%d9%86%d9%8a-%d9%84%d8%a7%d9%82%d9%84-%d9%85%d9%86-23-%d8%b3%d9%86%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%85%d8%a7-2/ |access-date=27 June 2023 |website=[[Royal Moroccan Football Federation]] |language=ar}}</ref> where the ''Atlas Lions'' won their first title,<ref name=":32">{{Cite web |date=8 July 2023 |title=Morocco win maiden TotalEnergies U-23 Africa Cup of Nations title with victory over Egypt {{!}} Total U-23 Africa Cup of Nations 2023 |url=https://www.cafonline.com/total-u23-africa-cup-of-nations/2023/news/morocco-win-maiden-totalenergies-u-23-africa-cup-of-nations-title-with-victory-o |access-date=9 July 2023 |website=CAFOnline.com}}</ref><ref name=":42">{{Cite web |date=9 July 2023 |title=Le Maroc remporte la CAN U23 au bout de la prolongation |url=https://www.sofoot.com/breves/can-u23-le-maroc-detrone-legypte-au-bout-de-la-prolongation |access-date=9 July 2023 |website=SO FOOT.com |language=fr-FR}}</ref> and qualified for the [[2024 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=":32" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=8 July 2023 |title=Le Mali, le Maroc et l'Égypte qualifiés pour les JO 2024 |url=https://www.sofoot.com/breves/le-mali-le-maroc-et-legypte-qualifies-pour-les-jo-2024 |access-date=9 July 2023 |website=SO FOOT.com |language=fr-FR}}</ref> On 21 March 2025, he scored his first international goal in a 2–1 victory over [[Niger national football team|Niger]] during the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2025/03/186517/morocco-triumphs-2-1-over-niger-in-world-cup-qualifier/ |title=Morocco Triumphs 2-1 Over Niger in World Cup Qualifier |publisher=Morocco World News |date=21 March 2025 }}</ref>

On 11 December 2025, El Khannouss was called up to the Morocco squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/morocco-name-star-studded-afcon-squad-as-hakimi-makes-cut-but-diop-misses-out/|title=Morocco name star-studded AFCON squad as Hakimi makes cut but Diop misses out|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=11 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

== Playing style ==
El Khannouss possesses exceptional control of the ball and great vision, qualities that allow him to excel in one-on-one situations and execute precise, defense-splitting passes. His playing style is characterized by his close ball control, agility, and the ability to navigate tight spaces. His former coach at [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]], [[Michel Ribeiro]], lauded him for having "eyes in his back," a testament to his ability to anticipate the movement of his teammates and opponents.<ref>{{Cite web |last=V |first=Sanjay Kumar |date=2025-07-30 |title=Tottenham identify Morgan Gibbs-White alternative who has "unbelievable feet and great vision" |url=https://tothelaneandback.com/2025/07/30/tottenham-identify-morgan-gibbs-white-alternative-who-has-unbelievable-feet-and-great-vision/ |access-date=2025-07-30 |website= |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=V |first=Sanjay |title=Bilal El Khannouss: Leicester midfielder with 'eyes in his back' and 'unbelievable feet' showing star quality in adversity |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11712/13307106/bilal-el-khannouss-leicester-midfielder-with-eyes-in-his-back-and-unbelievable-feet-showing-star-quality-in-adversity |archive-date= |access-date=2025-07-30}}</ref>

